        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 8:22PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 822 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Dortches, or near Nashville, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rocky Mount, Tarboro, Nashville, Dortches, Red Oak, Whitakers,
Leggett, Battleboro, and Kingsboro.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
